= page_title "Use SublimeVideo on an HTTPS site"

:textile
  SSL Serving of SublimeVideo Player is *free of charge for all paid plans*.

= raw "In order to use the SSL-served version of SublimeVideo, you have to check the #{content_tag(:em, '"Deliver with SSL for secure pages"')} checkbox in the embed code popup in the #{link_to content_tag(:em, '"My sites"'), sites_url(subdomain: 'my'), onclick: "window.open(this); return false"} page."

:textile
  If your site includes both HTTP and HTTPS pages, you can also use the following simple script that will load the right version of SublimeVideo depending on the page's current security level:

:coderay
  #{coderay_options(:javascript)}
  <script type="text/javascript">document.write(unescape("%3Cscript src='" + (("https:" == document.location.protocol) ? "https://4076.voxcdn.com" : "http://cdn.sublimevideo.net") + "/js/YOUR_TOKEN.js' type='text/javascript'%3E%3C/script%3E"));</script>
  
= raw "All you have to do is to replace #{content_tag(:em, 'YOUR_TOKEN')} with your actual site's token (find it in the embed code popup in the #{link_to content_tag(:em, '"My sites"'), sites_url(subdomain: 'my'), onclick: "window.open(this); return false"} page.)."
  